node.title: Teenage girl charged with murder after alleged stabbing in Queensland's Gulf
node.alt: A roadside sign in the outback  reads 'Welcome to Doomadgee'.
node.description: A teenage girl has been charged with murder in relation to the alleged stabbing of a 16-year-old boy in the remote Aboriginal town of Doomadgee, in Queensland's Gulf region.
node.content: ["A teenage girl has been charged with murder in relation to the alleged stabbing\u00a0of a\u00a016-year-old boy in the remote Aboriginal town of Doomadgee, in Queensland's Gulf region, on Tuesday.", "Detectives from Mount Isa District Child Protection and Investigation Unit and the Criminal Investigation Branch are investigating the death.", "It will be alleged an altercation occurred between the two teenagers\u00a0during which time the boy was stabbed at a Roberts Street address shortly after midday.", "The boy was pronounced deceased at the scene and the girl was taken into custody nearby.", "She has been denied police bail and remanded in custody to appear in the Doomadgee Children\u2019s Court charged with murder, domestic violence offence.", "More to come."]
